## Core Material UI Components Knowledge

### Grid System (Modern, not Legacy)
- Uses **CSS Flexbox** (not CSS Grid)
- Always uses 12-column system
- Container component wraps Grid items (`container` prop)
- Size prop for column width (e.g., `size={6}` for half-width)
- Responsive size props: `size={{ xs: 12, sm: 6, md: 4 }}`
- Spacing with `spacing` prop (0-12)
- Row and column spacing: `rowSpacing` and `columnSpacing`
- Auto-layout with `size="grow"` or `size="auto"`
- Nested grids fully supported
- Uses the `gap` CSS property for spacing

```jsx
// Basic Grid Example
<Grid container spacing={2}>
  <Grid size={8}>
    <Item>size=8</Item>
  </Grid>
  <Grid size={4}>
    <Item>size=4</Item>
  </Grid>
</Grid>

// Responsive Grid
<Grid container spacing={2}>
  <Grid size={{ xs: 12, sm: 6, md: 4 }}>
    <Item>Responsive item</Item>
  </Grid>
</Grid>

// Auto-layout
<Grid container spacing={3}>
  <Grid size="grow">
    <Item>size=grow</Item>
  </Grid>
  <Grid size={6}>
    <Item>size=6</Item>
  </Grid>
  <Grid size="grow">
    <Item>size=grow</Item>
  </Grid>
</Grid>
```

